article.headline: Ohio 51, Coppin St 47
article.story: CINCINNATI (AP) -- Jaivon Harris scored 17 points and grabbed five rebounds to lead Ohio to a 51-47 win over Coppin State on Sunday in a consolation game of the Black Coaches Association Classic. The Bobcats (1-1) never trailed after the first three minutes and overpowered Coppin State in the paint, outscoring them 24-14. Coppin State tied it at 42-42 with 7:02 left in the game on a layup by Raheem Scott -- his only points of the game. But Harris answered with a solo 7-0 streak to make it 49-42 with 4:20 left. The Eagles (0-2) were led by Jimmy Boykin, who came off the bench to score 14 points and add five rebounds. Nicholas King added 10 points, including a three-pointer at the final buzzer, and four assists.
